Regarding serious cases, patients rapidly developed acute respiratory syndrome, septic shock, metabolic acidosis, and coagulopathy.
Patients with fever and/or respiratory symptoms, as well as those with acute fever, even in the absence of thoracic radiographic anomalies, should be tested for the virus in order to allow early diagnosis.
