Three vaccination strategies are being researched.
First, researchers are trying to create an entire virus vaccine.
The use of such a virus, whether inactive or dead, is intended to cause a rapid immune response from the human body in the event of a new infection with COVID-19.
A second strategy, subunit-based vaccines, aims to create a vaccine that sensitizes the immune system to certain subunits of the virus.
In the case of SARS-CoV-2, these studies focus on S-specule protein that helps the virus to infiltrate into the ACE 2 enzyme receptor.
A third strategy is that of nuclear acid-based vaccines (ADN or NRA vaccination, a new vaccination technique).
